HEADWORD: Whaleback
<hw>Whale"back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A form of vessel, often with steam power, having sharp ends and a
very convex upper deck, much used on the Great Lakes, esp. for carrying
grain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whaleboat</ent>⟦br⟧
